text: A minimart is conveniently located at Block 139, Simei St 1 serving the neighbourhood so that residents living around the area need not travel further to Eastpoint Mall (which is about one bus-stop away or 5 minutes of walk) to get their groceries and other household items. You can get the very basic foodstuffs (e.g. bread loaves, fresh milk, soft drinks, etc.) and household items here.

there's a good mix of fresh vegetables and a few types of frozen chicken meat. sell alot of cooking condiments and other home necessities like pads and toilet paper. basically they got everything u would need dont need go ntuc. only thing is maybe certain things are slightly costly.
